  "wikitext": "\n'''2-1-060\n\nLumen per Square Metre\n\nThe SI Unit: of illuminance. The illuminance produced by a luminous flux of one lumen uniformly distributed over a surface of area one square metre.\n\nSymbol: lx, lm/m2 1 lx = 1 lm/m2\n\nOther metric Unit: phot (ph)\n\nNon-metric units footcandle (fc)\n\nsea-mile candela (s.m.c.)\n\n1 fc = 1 lumen per square foot (lm/ft2)\n\n1 s.m.c. = 1 lumen per square sea-mile\n\n1 lx = 10-4 phot = footcandle\n\n= 3.43 x 106 sea-mile candela\n\nC.I.E.(modified)\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Lux}}\n[[Category:2.1 Optics and Vision]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]"
